CHANGES
=======

Unreleased (2026-03-07)

- chore(release): add package-local `release:preflight` support so a single package can run cleanbuild, tests, and local release checks from its own directory.
- chore(release): stop using `setup-node` pnpm caching in the GitHub CLI release workflow because this repo does not ship a `pnpm-lock.yaml`.
- chore(release): install workspace dependencies with `pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile --link-workspace-packages` in the GitHub CLI release workflow because this repo does not ship a `pnpm-lock.yaml` and the CLI depends on the local prerelease client package.
- chore(release): add a repo-level pnpm build-script allowlist for `sqlite3` and `esbuild`, while explicitly blocking `@scarf/scarf`, so clean GitHub installs can run the shared test/build pipeline before publishing the CLI.
- (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: openai-gpt-5-codex/medium).)

Version 2.0.0-beta1 (2026-03-07)

- chore(release): stage the `2.0.0-beta1` prerelease and align package metadata with it.
- chore(release): add a GitHub Actions CLI release workflow that verifies, packs, publishes to npm on tag pushes, and creates a GitHub Release.
- chore(package): replace the internal `workspace:*` client dependency with a publishable `^2.0.0-beta1` range and add a `files` whitelist for the public CLI tarball.
- chore(release): add shared local/CI release verification tooling plus a local `npm publish --dry-run` path so package publication can be smoke-tested before tagging.
- (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: openai-gpt-5-codex/medium).)

Version 1.0.4 (2026-03-06)

- feat(cli): add `mm-cli reload` command to trigger a server-side force-reload via the API.
- fix(push-dir): preserve newer form config fields and patch returned `form_key` values even when a form inherits locale from the domain default.
- test(push-dir): add regression coverage for form field round-tripping and inherited-locale `--patch-source-ids` write-back.
- (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: openai-gpt-5-codex/medium).)

Version 1.0.3 (2026-03-05)

- fix(cli): parse `--part false` correctly instead of treating any non-empty string as truthy.
- (Changes generated/assisted by Claude Code (profile: anthropic-claude-opus-4-6/high).)

Version 1.0.2 (2026-03-04)

- fix(preprocess): correctly preserve child block overrides across multi-level `{% extends %}` chains during template merge.
- test(preprocess): add regression coverage for three-level template inheritance to prevent override loss.
- fix(cli): reject absolute/traversing template `filename` values from `init-data.json` when resolving tx/form template paths.
- test(cli): add regression coverage for rejecting unsafe `filename` path traversal during `compileConfigTree`.
- feat(cli): add opt-in `MMCLI_ALLOW_UNSAFE_TEMPLATE_PATHS` env flag for legacy imports that depend on absolute or traversing template `filename` values.
- feat(cli): support natural-key domain mapping (`domain` name) in config records for compile/push flows; treat numeric `domain_id` as optional hints.
- feat(cli): add `push-dir` write-back controls (`--patch-source-ids`, `--backup`) for opt-in source mutation of resolved IDs/keys.
- feat(cli): add opt-in source patching of resolved `form_key` values back into `init-data.json`.
- fix(cli): remove local `push-dir` lock/state file handling (`.mail-magic-sync.json`) to avoid a false sense of cross-process safety.
- docs(cli): document `MMCLI_ALLOW_UNSAFE_TEMPLATE_PATHS` in `.mmcli-env` settings.
- docs(cli): document `push-dir` write-back flags and natural-key domain mapping support.
- (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: chatgpt-5.3-codex/medium).)

Version 1.0.1 (2026-02-22)

- chore(release): add package-level `release:check` script and wire `release` to shared publish script.
- chore(scripts): replace `rm -rf` cleanup scripts with `rimraf`.
- test(logging): quiet package test output by default (silent Vitest + silent shared-sync step).
- test(examples): add a compile smoke test that compiles `packages/server/examples/data` via `compileConfigTree`.
- fix(cli): defer `loadCliEnv()` from module load time to just before `program.parse()`, preventing file-system side effects when the module is imported at startup; apply env-file defaults via `setOptionValueWithSource` so CLI flags still override them correctly.
- docs(readme): document the `version` command, the `--css` parameter for `compile`/`push`/`push-dir`, and the `--skip-tx`/`--skip-forms` flags for `push-dir`.
- (Changes generated/assisted by Claude Code (profile: anthropic-claude-sonnet-4-6/high).)
- (Changes generated/assisted by Codex (profile: chatgpt-5.3-codex/medium).)

